com.ibm.mq.explorer.ms0s.mqsceditor.rules

Class MQSCStatefulRule

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ibm.mq.explorer.ms0s.mqsceditor.rules.MQSCStatefulRule
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.eclipse.jface.text.rules.IRule

    public class MQSCStatefulRule
extends java.lang.Object
implements org.eclipse.jface.text.rules.IRule

    This is the rule that uses state information on the text it had arleady seen to ensure that the current bits of text are valid. It uses the MQSCLanugageConfigurator to identify specific data in the text and merely focuses on what state it's in and what type of token is next.
